      "date": "2015-11-13 21:00:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThe patch looks reasonable in itself (minor whitespace fix only needed if patch is refreshed for some other reason).\n\nIt do anything to fix the client LASSERT(), which should never be done on data that is received over the network.  It would be good to have a second patch to apply to the client that replaces the LASSERT() with a proper sanity check and error return, so that new clients using older servers do not crash for the same reason.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
